More than six months after announcing plans to sell Hoover, the vacuum-cleaner maker, Whirlpool may be close to a deal. Reuters, citing an unnamed source, reported Friday that a sale to a private equity firm was imminent, though it did not identify the firm or indicate a price. An announcement could come as soon as next week, Reuters said. Whirlpool, which makes a range of household appliances, picked up Hoover in last year’s $1.7 billion acquisition of rival Maytag.

